==English==

===Etymology===
From the name of the Thaypan tribe of [[Aboriginal]] people of central [[Cape York Peninsula]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].

===Noun===
'''taipan''' (''plural:'' '''[[taipans]]''')

Extremely venemous species of snakes of the family ''[[Elapidae]]''. The Coastal Taipan (''Oxyuranus scutellatus scutellatus''), and the Inland Taipan or Fierce Snake, (''Oxyuranus microlepidotus''), are both  found in Australia, while the Papuan Taipan (''Oxyuranus scutellatus canniis'') is found in southern coastal [[New Guinea]].


